		<li>
			<p>
				<strong>Qus: 10</strong>
				What is the use of name and value attributes? Give two examples 		
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Ans:</strong>
				The name value attribute specifies the name and it can help reference an element in javascript.
				For example, if I click a button on a form - the name attribute of the button is listed with the received user input on the form. 
				The value attribute represents the value of an element.
				For example if I click a button on a form - the value of that button determines the input received on the form.
				<!-- a 3rd example would be: <button name="pie" type="submit" value="pecan">Pecan</button>
					- the above would show: pie=pecan for user input -->
			</p>
		</li>
